even better because at SoCraTes we manage to\nbring a critical mass of mindful humans together that actively push for\ninclusivity and safety at tech conferences. This mindset permeates permeates\nevery thing that happens at the conference which enables newcomers to quickly\nopen up and contribute with their entire self."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Nevertheless I felt the urge to make a statement."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I had visited two open-space conferences this year who are part of the\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"ever growing community of Software Crafters"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.softwarecrafters.org/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\naround the world. And at these events diversity was lacking, which was due to\ntheir geographical situation. However, living in Norway, I totally get that it\nis sometimes impossible to achieve diversity amongst event attendee if the\nstructure of the industry itself is absolutely dominated by men."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The issue then arises is when attendees use English as the common language and\naddress the entire room as "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Guys"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I am absolutely aware that for many it's not a conscious decision, and they did\nnot intend to address everyone as "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"men"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", but are using "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"guys"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" in a\ngender-neutral form."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"However"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" many are painfully aware of the literal translation because they are\nnon-native speakers and did not grow up with "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Hey guys!"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" being used as an idiom\nand not as a way to selectively address the male members of a group."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"After all "},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Guys"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" is not gender neutral"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":":"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"https://twitter.com/etiene_d/status/994509163693838337?embed"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://twitter.com/etiene_d/status/994509163693838337?embed","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Not convinced? Please read "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"this"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.xaprb.com/blog/you-guys/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\nextensive post about the topic."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#calling-everyone-a-guy--is-one-of-these-microaggressions-that-keep-reminding-some-members-of-our-community-that-they-are-not-recognized-%EF%B8%8F","ariaLabel":"calling everyone a guy  is one of these microaggressions that keep reminding some members of our community that they are not recognized Ô∏è permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Calling everyone a Guy ü§µ is one of these microaggressions that keep reminding some members of our community that they are not recognized. ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"calling-everyone-a-guy--is-one-of-these-microaggressions-that-keep-reminding-some-members-of-our-community-that-they-are-not-recognized-Ô∏è","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Now, changing behaviour is "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"hard"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". And especially at events I find it impolite\nto interrupt someone (especially in public) if they use "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Guys"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". They most likely\nare not aware how it makes others feel and there is a high chance that it puts\nthem in a spotlight which in most times will make them turn into\naggressive-defensive mode rather than considering their behaviour."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"This holds true for online communities as well. It is much more helpful to reach\nout to a person in a private chat and ask them to consider their wording then\npointing it out in the public thread. There they even have the chance to edit\ntheir postings."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"This obviously is not possible at events."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#this-t-shirt-is-like-a-friendly-virus","ariaLabel":"this t shirt is like a friendly virus pe